  <data name="label39.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Sections only race if they are Enabled in "Race Sections (irc)".

• Every race needs a mapping: select IRC section + CBFTP section, click Map,
  then set a trigger regex (.* matches everything) and Save it.

• Section Rules are global for the IRC section. Tag Rules are only for the
  selected mapping. Order: Section DROP → Tag Rules → Section ALLOW → default ALLOW.

• PRE Regex are only used for AFFIL racing (prebot lines).
  Affiliates are configured on the CBFTP site itself, not in RaceTrade.

• When a site uses GLOBAL PREBOT, the regex comes from the global prebot
  config, not from this site’s own Pre Regex fields. Make sure you use the irc categories 
  of the prebot announce, not the site.

• If nothing is racing, enable Debug Mode and check Application + Race logs
  to see which mapping/rule matched or why it was dropped.</value>
  </data>
